## Notes
- `tau_rad` is set by the day-night amplitude (strong); `tau_drag` by the hot-spot offset (weak) and is expected to be broader / correlated with `tau_rad`.
- priors: tau_rad [h]~log10_uniform[0.5,48], tau_drag [h]~log10_uniform[0.5,48], F_p/F_s~log10_uniform[0.0001,0.008], Phibar~log10_uniform[2e+06,8e+06], DPhieq~log10_uniform[5e+05,5e+06], sigma scale~log10_uniform[0.5,5]

